WEBVTT

00:03.699 --> 00:04.047
.

00:04.091 --> 00:06.006
- I wanted to meet my
daughter,

00:06.049 --> 00:07.007
but I had nothing to do
with her

00:07.050 --> 00:08.486
being hired by this hospital.

00:08.530 --> 00:13.013
- I'm so grateful
that you're in my life.

00:13.056 --> 00:14.318
- The Vas-COM business,

00:14.362 --> 00:16.059
playing nice with the enemy,
it sucked.

00:16.103 --> 00:17.974
The device rep, Jessa,

00:18.018 --> 00:19.715
did you sleep with her to get
the information you needed?

00:19.758 --> 00:22.152
- No.
- Good.

00:22.196 --> 00:23.849
- My firm's been meeting
with patients

00:23.893 --> 00:25.460
and families affected
by the Vas-COM.

00:25.503 --> 00:28.245
- Will you get a case?
- Oh, yeah. Good one.

00:28.289 --> 00:29.594
- Randall Shentu.

00:29.638 --> 00:31.857
The board brought me on
to help Med

00:31.901 --> 00:33.163
through this challenging time.

00:33.207 --> 00:36.471
A scandal is playing out.
Med's in trouble.

00:36.514 --> 00:38.690
- The focus should be
on Matthew Cooper

00:38.734 --> 00:41.519
being accountable
and going to prison.

00:41.563 --> 00:43.347
- There's something
I've been wanting to say.

00:43.391 --> 00:44.522
- I'm not interested.

00:44.566 --> 00:46.611
- You come at me
as hard as you want.

00:46.655 --> 00:48.222
[dramatic music]

00:50.137 --> 00:51.834
- Thanks for coming out.

00:51.877 --> 00:53.227
- All good. What's going on?

00:53.270 --> 00:55.229
- We got called out on a noise
disturbance,

00:55.272 --> 00:56.926
Carmen and Terrell.

00:56.969 --> 01:00.538
They were arguing and violent.
He took off before we got here.

01:00.582 --> 01:03.106
- You said something
about their son

01:03.150 --> 01:04.542
and something with his arm.

01:04.586 --> 01:06.196
- Yeah.
It's what the fight was about.

01:06.240 --> 01:07.719
Carmen said
it didn't look right.

01:07.763 --> 01:09.634
Wanna take him to the hospital,
but Terrell said,

01:09.678 --> 01:13.334
"No, money's tight."
Thought you should take a look.

01:15.292 --> 01:17.512
When's the last time
you saw them?

01:17.555 --> 01:20.080
- [sighs]
Twelve years.

01:20.123 --> 01:22.125
- You sure you cool with this?

01:22.169 --> 01:24.388
- Yeah, yeah, yeah. I'm fine.

01:24.432 --> 01:26.390
- All right, man.
- Yeah.

01:26.434 --> 01:29.567
[apprehensive music]

01:29.611 --> 01:32.918
♪

01:32.962 --> 01:34.137
- Dylan?

01:34.181 --> 01:35.921
- Hey, Carmen.

01:35.965 --> 01:37.575
- What are you doing here?

01:37.619 --> 01:39.229
- Zora called.

01:39.273 --> 01:41.275
Said your son
might've hurt his arm.

01:41.318 --> 01:43.015
So I figured
I come take a look.

01:43.059 --> 01:44.539
- Yeah.

01:44.582 --> 01:46.889
Come in. I'm sorry. Come in.

01:49.196 --> 01:52.024
- That him?
- Yeah, Darius.

01:52.068 --> 01:53.200
Come here, sweetie.

01:53.243 --> 01:55.593
- Hey, man. I'm Dr. Scott.

01:55.637 --> 01:57.943
You mind if I take
a look at your arm?

01:57.987 --> 01:59.597
- Okay.

01:59.641 --> 02:03.166
- All right. Let's see. Okay.

02:04.559 --> 02:06.778
Is it all right
if I press it a little bit?

02:08.084 --> 02:10.695
- Ow!
- I'm sorry. Sorry.

02:10.739 --> 02:12.523
How long has it been
hurting like that?

02:12.567 --> 02:15.700
- A couple days.
- Hmm. All right.

02:15.744 --> 02:18.138
I wanna talk
to your mom for a second.

02:18.181 --> 02:19.835
All right.

02:19.878 --> 02:22.490
[clears throat]

02:22.533 --> 02:24.579
You were right to think
to take him to the hospital.

02:24.622 --> 02:26.581
I'm concerned his arm
might be broken.

02:26.624 --> 02:28.452
- That's what I told Terrell.

02:28.496 --> 02:29.845
He got laid off
a couple weeks ago

02:29.888 --> 02:32.239
so he's just been worried
about paying the bills.

02:32.282 --> 02:35.329
- I understand.
- Yeah.

02:35.372 --> 02:37.809
Okay, sweetie.
Let's get your coat on, okay?

02:37.853 --> 02:44.816
♪

02:44.860 --> 02:45.817
- Hey.

02:45.861 --> 02:47.297
- What?

02:47.341 --> 02:48.994
- Quite a look
you got going on.

02:49.038 --> 02:51.214
Planning on hitting the lanes?

02:51.258 --> 02:52.824
- It's mostly just
a fashion statement,

02:52.868 --> 02:55.479
but I do enjoy rolling
the occasional game.

02:55.523 --> 02:58.439
- Anyway, coming in
on your day off, what gives?

02:58.482 --> 03:00.223
- All the paperwork
since this lawsuit started,

03:00.267 --> 03:01.442
I haven't had a minute
to catch up.

03:01.485 --> 03:02.530
- Tell me about it.

03:02.573 --> 03:05.489
I just got here,
I'm already behind.

03:05.533 --> 03:06.795
But more importantly,

03:06.838 --> 03:10.190
do you have the matching shoes
in your car?

03:10.233 --> 03:12.757
- Wouldn't you like to know?

03:12.801 --> 03:15.151
- Please, somebody!

03:15.195 --> 03:17.675
- Hey.

03:17.719 --> 03:19.242
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hey, someone get me a gurney.

03:19.286 --> 03:20.939
Hey, hey, hey,
it's okay, sweetie.

03:20.983 --> 03:22.419
What's your name?
- Nadia.

03:22.463 --> 03:24.552
- Nadia. I'm Dr. Hammer.
I'm gonna help you, okay?

03:24.595 --> 03:26.815
Can you tell me what happened?
- [groans]

03:26.858 --> 03:28.382
- Just stick with me here.
I need to take a look.

03:28.425 --> 03:32.995
[tense music]

03:33.038 --> 03:34.388
Did you have surgery?

03:34.431 --> 03:36.346
Nadia? Nadia?

03:36.390 --> 03:39.436
Nadia? Where's that gurney?

03:39.480 --> 03:43.919
♪

03:47.923 --> 03:48.140
.

03:48.184 --> 03:49.185
[knock at door]

03:49.229 --> 03:50.360
- Come in.

03:51.927 --> 03:53.755
- Morning.
- Good morning.

03:55.452 --> 03:58.063
- Café macchiato with 2%.

03:58.107 --> 04:01.763
- I suspect you're not here
just to bring me coffee.

04:01.806 --> 04:03.547
- Okay, I'm wondering

04:03.591 --> 04:06.071
why you still haven't sat down
with Avery Quinn.

04:06.115 --> 04:08.944
- Because her firm is bringing
a class action lawsuit

04:08.987 --> 04:11.338
against this hospital,
and frankly,

04:11.381 --> 04:14.645
I don't think we should be
so eager to cooperate.

04:14.689 --> 04:16.343
- Ms. Goodwin,
these depositions

04:16.386 --> 04:18.867
are just pro forma
to check all the boxes.

04:18.910 --> 04:21.304
- This lawsuit shouldn't
be happening.

04:21.348 --> 04:25.700
Every one of our doctors
associated with the Vas-COM

04:25.743 --> 04:27.397
is listed as defendants,

04:27.441 --> 04:30.052
but they didn't do
anything wrong.

04:30.095 --> 04:31.706
They shouldn't be punished.

04:31.749 --> 04:32.924
- You're right.

04:32.968 --> 04:35.753
But what we need
to avoid right now

04:35.797 --> 04:39.322
is an ugly legal battle that
gets played out in the media

04:39.366 --> 04:42.194
because the place where
we're really being judged

04:42.238 --> 04:45.328
is in the court
of public opinion.

04:45.372 --> 04:49.637
Just think about it,
and enjoy the macchiato.

04:49.680 --> 04:52.596
[suspenseful music]

04:52.640 --> 04:57.775
♪

04:57.819 --> 04:59.951
- Mr. Shaw, how we feeling?

04:59.995 --> 05:01.431
- Much better.

05:01.475 --> 05:03.259
- So good news,
troponins are negative.

05:03.303 --> 05:04.434
EKG is normal.

05:04.478 --> 05:06.044
Your fall was not caused
by a heart attack.

05:06.088 --> 05:09.352
- Thank God. And my wrist?

05:09.396 --> 05:12.137
- Just a sprain,
but let me ask,

05:12.181 --> 05:14.531
anything causing you
extra anxiety these days?

05:14.575 --> 05:15.750
- Uh--
- Do you mind?

05:15.793 --> 05:17.229
- Business just
hasn't been great.

05:17.273 --> 05:20.102
I'm not getting much sleep.

05:20.145 --> 05:21.799
A doctor gave me beta blockers

05:21.843 --> 05:22.887
for when I start
to feel stressed.

05:22.931 --> 05:24.454
But today I felt like

05:24.498 --> 05:26.282
there was an elephant
standing on my chest.

05:26.326 --> 05:28.632
- Well, you did
the right thing coming here.

05:28.676 --> 05:29.938
Panic attacks can feel exactly

05:29.981 --> 05:32.288
like you're having
a heart attack.

05:32.332 --> 05:36.248
- So next time I should just
take the pills my doc gave me?

05:36.292 --> 05:38.816
- Well, beta blockers
do often work well,

05:38.860 --> 05:40.818
but I suggest you follow up
with your doctor

05:40.862 --> 05:42.820
and come up with
a good long term plan

05:42.864 --> 05:44.779
for handling your anxiety
moving forward.

05:44.822 --> 05:46.302
- Will do.

05:46.346 --> 05:47.912
- And Sean here's
gonna wrap your wrist,

05:47.956 --> 05:49.087
and then we'll
get you outta here, okay?

05:49.131 --> 05:50.524
- Thanks, doc.
- You bet.

05:51.916 --> 05:53.004
- Dr. Marcel.
- Yeah.

05:53.048 --> 05:54.528
- We got a patient coming in.

05:54.571 --> 05:55.964
- Okay.
- Wes Tucker.

05:56.007 --> 05:58.445
- Wes Tucker?
Hall of Fame Wes Tucker?

05:58.488 --> 06:00.664
- Hey, uh, let's take him
to trauma three.

06:00.708 --> 06:02.971
A little more private.

06:03.014 --> 06:04.712
- We got a 42-year-old male
in liver failure,

06:04.755 --> 06:09.064
BP 92/ 60, heart rate 112.
Gave him fluids in the field.

06:09.107 --> 06:11.022
- Mr. Tucker,
I'm Randall Shentu.

06:11.066 --> 06:12.197
These are doctors
Blake and Marcel,

06:12.241 --> 06:13.634
two of our very best.

06:13.677 --> 06:15.984
If there's anything you need,
please let me know.

06:16.027 --> 06:17.594
- Appreciate it, sir.

06:17.638 --> 06:18.856
- All right, guys. Here we go.

06:18.900 --> 06:22.164
- I need a FAST scan, CBC,
CMP, LFTs, coags,

06:22.207 --> 06:23.818
tox screen, and a hep panel.

06:23.861 --> 06:24.949
- Copy that.
- All right.

06:24.993 --> 06:26.037
Here we go,
transfer on my count.

06:26.081 --> 06:27.996
One, two, three.

06:28.039 --> 06:31.391
♪

06:31.434 --> 06:33.654
How you doing, Mr. Tucker?
How long you been vomiting for?

06:33.697 --> 06:35.395
- About a day and a half.

06:35.438 --> 06:36.874
Thumb drive's got
my medical info.

06:36.918 --> 06:39.137
Excuse me.
- Okay.

06:39.181 --> 06:40.095
- Dorris.
- Yeah.

06:40.138 --> 06:41.444
- Look at him.

06:41.488 --> 06:43.011
[camera shutter snaps]

06:43.054 --> 06:44.404
- Shut that.

06:48.146 --> 06:49.539
- Take deep breaths for me.

06:49.583 --> 06:52.847
- [breathes deeply]
- There you go.

06:52.890 --> 06:54.414
- No free fluid.

06:57.504 --> 07:00.985
- Liver on his CT looks
nodular and cirrhotic.

07:01.029 --> 07:03.248
Atrophy of the right lobe
and splenomegaly.

07:04.989 --> 07:07.731
- How long you been
an alcoholic?

07:07.775 --> 07:10.081
- You don't beat
around the bush.

07:10.125 --> 07:12.040
- How long?

07:12.083 --> 07:13.998
- Long as I can remember.

07:14.042 --> 07:16.697
Tried to stop,
been in and out of rehab.

07:16.740 --> 07:21.919
Just fell off the wagon again.

07:21.963 --> 07:23.225
- Let's give him
four milligrams Zofran

07:23.268 --> 07:25.096
for his nausea, please.

07:25.140 --> 07:26.707
- We're gonna run some labs,
but I'm pretty sure

07:26.750 --> 07:28.230
you're in
fulminant liver failure,

07:28.273 --> 07:29.927
and you're gonna need
a transplant.

07:31.799 --> 07:34.628
I'll get my team on it,
and we'll check back.

07:34.671 --> 07:39.937
♪

07:39.981 --> 07:42.592
All right, everybody,
show's over.

07:42.636 --> 07:43.985
Back to work.

07:50.034 --> 07:52.472
- Hey, is that the young woman
who collapsed in the lobby?

07:52.515 --> 07:54.865
- Yeah.
- What's going on?

07:54.909 --> 07:57.389
- It's the weirdest thing, I--
just hold on a sec.

07:57.433 --> 07:59.914
Dr. Charles,
do you have a minute?

07:59.957 --> 08:01.611
- Yeah, what's up?

08:01.655 --> 08:05.615
- My patient in three is septic
from gluteal implant surgery.

08:05.659 --> 08:08.096
But the thing is, she won't
tell me who did it or where.

08:08.139 --> 08:11.099
- Is she otherwise being,
you know, transparent

08:11.142 --> 08:12.579
about her history
and stuff, medical history?

08:12.622 --> 08:13.971
- Yeah.

08:14.015 --> 08:16.017
- You think this is something

08:16.060 --> 08:17.801
illegal,
some back alley surgery?

08:17.845 --> 08:19.542
- I do.
- Yeah.

08:19.586 --> 08:22.414
Could be.
Why don't I have a quick chat?

08:22.458 --> 08:23.720
- That'd be great. Thanks.

08:23.764 --> 08:25.026
- Of course.

08:31.989 --> 08:33.469
- Hey, Maggie.

08:33.513 --> 08:36.080
- Oh, and good morning.
- [chuckles]

08:36.124 --> 08:38.822
So my parents have been asking

08:38.866 --> 08:41.303
if you wanted to come over
for a family dinner.

08:41.346 --> 08:43.479
They wanna get to know you.

08:43.523 --> 08:44.654
- They wanna get to know me?
- Yeah.

08:44.698 --> 08:46.395
I--I've been kind of nervous
to ask,

08:46.438 --> 08:48.353
but what are you doing tonight?

08:48.397 --> 08:49.964
- Tonight?
- I know.

08:50.007 --> 08:51.574
I know it's so last minute,
but tonight's lasagna night,

08:51.618 --> 08:53.968
and that's, like,
my mom's specialty, so.

08:54.011 --> 08:56.927
- Well, it sounds like fun.
I mean--

08:56.971 --> 09:01.062
- Hey, Mags, you got a second?
I need help in five.

09:01.105 --> 09:03.673
- Yeah. I'm sorry.

09:07.938 --> 09:10.680
- All right, D-man,
let's get you in this chair.

09:12.639 --> 09:17.382
- And I am going
to take you to X-ray.

09:17.426 --> 09:20.081
- You nervous, sweetie?
- A little.

09:20.124 --> 09:23.214
- Oh, no way you nervous
with those Bordeauxs on.

09:23.258 --> 09:27.175
Check me out. Pow.
[chuckles]

09:27.218 --> 09:30.221
Yeah. You cool?

09:30.265 --> 09:32.789
- Yeah, but I'm not very good.

09:34.095 --> 09:36.184
- Let me tell you something.

09:36.227 --> 09:37.402
Me neither.

09:40.188 --> 09:42.016
- Okay.

09:42.059 --> 09:43.626
Here we go.

09:49.327 --> 09:52.679
- Hey, big guy.

09:52.722 --> 09:54.158
Where's he going?

09:54.202 --> 09:56.204
- To get an X-ray for his arm.

09:56.247 --> 09:57.858
- All right.
Then I'll take him.

09:57.901 --> 09:58.859
Come on, I'll drive.

09:58.902 --> 10:00.295
- Actually, Terrell,

10:00.338 --> 10:02.993
it's authorized
medical personnel only.

10:03.037 --> 10:06.736
- Officer Scott.
It's nice to see you.

10:06.780 --> 10:08.869
- Look, it's hospital
policy, man.

10:08.912 --> 10:12.046
- Come on. This is my kid.
Can't bend the rules?

10:12.089 --> 10:14.788
- Come on.
Tarrell, Darius is hurt.

10:14.831 --> 10:17.704
Give it a rest.

10:17.747 --> 10:19.053
We're ready.

10:19.096 --> 10:20.663
- Mm-hmm.

10:20.707 --> 10:23.666
[tense music]

10:23.710 --> 10:28.715
♪

10:28.758 --> 10:30.760
- Uh, everything okay?

10:30.804 --> 10:33.154
- Yeah, it's complicated.

10:33.197 --> 10:36.374
Knew them from way back.

10:36.418 --> 10:38.725
Three of us used to be
best friends, inseparable,

10:38.768 --> 10:40.944
and now we've gone
different ways.

10:40.988 --> 10:42.250
- Well, that happens.

10:42.293 --> 10:44.208
And didn't sound
that complicated.

10:44.252 --> 10:46.558
Yeah, well, Carmen and I

10:46.602 --> 10:48.256
started a thing,
then we broke up.

10:48.299 --> 10:49.431
- Oh, I see.

10:49.474 --> 10:51.259
Well, he got her
on the rebound, right?

10:51.302 --> 10:54.915
- Something like that,
but there's more to it.

10:54.958 --> 10:57.657
- So should I be thinking
of taking you off this case?

10:57.700 --> 11:01.138
- No, no, no, no. I'm fine.
It was a long time ago.

11:02.183 --> 11:03.967
- Yeah?

11:04.011 --> 11:06.274
- Look, I owe it to Terrell,
and I promised Carmen

11:06.317 --> 11:07.710
that I would take care of this.

11:07.754 --> 11:08.711
- Okay.

11:12.802 --> 11:16.153
- Dr. Blake, Dr. Marcel,
may I have a word?

11:16.197 --> 11:17.415
- Sure.

11:21.158 --> 11:22.638
- We have good news.

11:22.682 --> 11:26.250
A liver just became available
for Wes Tucker.

11:26.294 --> 11:27.817
So get your team ready.

11:27.861 --> 11:30.124
It should land here in
under two hours.

11:30.167 --> 11:32.909
- Unfortunately, we can't.

11:32.953 --> 11:35.129
Mr. Tucker's tox screen
just came back.

11:35.172 --> 11:37.305
- He tested positive
for alcohol.

11:37.348 --> 11:38.915
Admitted he's an alcoholic.

11:38.959 --> 11:40.569
- And since you have to be
six months sober in order

11:40.612 --> 11:43.224
to get a liver
off the transplant list,

11:43.267 --> 11:45.182
we have no choice but to pass.

11:45.226 --> 11:47.663
- But the man's gravely ill.

11:47.707 --> 11:49.926
Without the transplant,
he could die.

11:49.970 --> 11:53.538
And the positive publicity
from saving Wes Tucker's life

11:53.582 --> 11:56.759
would not only encourage
future organ donation,

11:56.803 --> 11:59.544
it would also help to build
back the hospital's good image.

11:59.588 --> 12:03.200
- And I understand that,
but the rules are the rules.

12:03.244 --> 12:04.811
- They're not our rules,
Mr. Shentu,

12:04.854 --> 12:06.682
they're dictated by UNOS.

12:06.726 --> 12:08.728
So unfortunately, we can't
do the transplant.

12:10.730 --> 12:11.948
Okay?

12:19.434 --> 12:19.782
.

12:19.826 --> 12:22.742
- Well, she definitely does not
wanna talk about her surgery.

12:22.785 --> 12:23.917
- Did you get anything?

12:23.960 --> 12:25.875
- Just, you know,
definitely get the sense

12:25.919 --> 12:27.529
that she's protecting somebody.

12:27.572 --> 12:28.965
- Yeah.

12:29.009 --> 12:31.185
- Oh, Dr. Hammer, Dr. Charles,
this is Nadia's dad.

12:31.228 --> 12:33.491
- Gregor.
May I see her, please?

12:33.535 --> 12:35.276
- Of course. Yeah.

12:39.715 --> 12:43.284
- Nadia, how you feeling?

12:43.327 --> 12:45.721
You gave your mother
and me a terrible scare.

12:50.639 --> 12:53.642
- The doctors have been
taking good care of me.

12:53.685 --> 12:56.863
- Good.
What has happened to her?

12:56.906 --> 13:00.170
- Is it okay?

13:00.214 --> 13:03.957
Well, she had surgery,
and the wound is infected.

13:04.000 --> 13:05.175
She has a blood infection now,

13:05.219 --> 13:06.698
and it's traveled
throughout her body.

13:06.742 --> 13:11.791
- Oh, my God.
Nadia, when did it start?

13:11.834 --> 13:13.357
- I had a little fever
last night.

13:15.272 --> 13:17.840
- My poor girl.

13:17.884 --> 13:20.321
Doctors,
may we speak for a moment?

13:20.364 --> 13:21.365
- Yeah.

13:25.717 --> 13:28.329
- My daughter,
is she going to be okay?

13:28.372 --> 13:31.636
- I hope so, but right now
she's in septic shock.

13:31.680 --> 13:33.421
The first 24 hours
are critical.

13:33.464 --> 13:35.118
- I understand.

13:35.162 --> 13:37.642
Did something go wrong
with her surgery?

13:37.686 --> 13:40.341
- As far as we can see
the surgery itself looks good,

13:40.384 --> 13:42.865
but we don't know what
kind of implants were used.

13:42.909 --> 13:44.824
- I mean, we're actually
having a hard time getting

13:44.867 --> 13:47.522
any kinda detail at all,
and we're wondering

13:47.565 --> 13:49.480
if you might be able
to help us out with that.

13:49.524 --> 13:55.312
- I wish I could, but you know
how it goes when kids grow up.

13:55.356 --> 13:58.359
We don't talk much,
but if she tells me anything...

13:58.402 --> 14:01.231
- Yeah, please let us know.
- I will. May I?

14:01.275 --> 14:02.406
- Yeah.

14:02.450 --> 14:06.193
[suspenseful music]

14:06.236 --> 14:08.499
- That seemed a little odd
to you?

14:08.543 --> 14:10.937
The way she reacted to him,
it was just--

14:10.980 --> 14:13.461
seemed, I don't know,
it was odd.

14:13.504 --> 14:15.506
- Yeah, he did say
they haven't spoken in a while.

14:15.550 --> 14:17.334
- Mm-Hmm. Could be it.

14:17.378 --> 14:18.640
- All right.
Let's check back in a bit.

14:18.683 --> 14:19.815
- Okay.

14:19.859 --> 14:23.863
♪

14:26.387 --> 14:30.217
- Just got Darius's
X-ray results in.

14:30.260 --> 14:31.827
- I'll be right back,
okay, sweetie?

14:31.871 --> 14:33.524
Okay.

14:33.568 --> 14:36.223
- Hi.
- Hi.

14:36.266 --> 14:39.661
- So his arm is indeed broken,
and it's a bit more complicated

14:39.704 --> 14:41.402
of a break
than what we usually see,

14:41.445 --> 14:43.665
which is why I've consulted
our surgeon, Dr. Archer here.

14:43.708 --> 14:44.753
- Whoa, whoa, wait, wait.

14:44.796 --> 14:46.146
Well, can't you just
give him a cast?

14:46.189 --> 14:47.408
- Well,
it's a two-bone fracture,

14:47.451 --> 14:49.366
which means that we will
need to use a plate.

14:49.410 --> 14:51.499
- A plate. What?
Are you kidding me?

14:51.542 --> 14:53.196
Now, you said he was here
to help Darius.

14:53.240 --> 14:55.242
- Okay, Terrell.
- No, listen to the guy.

14:55.285 --> 14:57.157
- Terrell, they're just
trying to help.

15:00.551 --> 15:02.292
[apprehensive music]

15:02.336 --> 15:05.382
- Now, if this was your kid,
what would you do?

15:05.426 --> 15:07.602
- Well, actually, my son
had a similar injury.

15:07.645 --> 15:10.344
I opted for the surgery.

15:10.387 --> 15:12.999
Without it,
he would've suffered pain

15:13.042 --> 15:14.870
and mobility issues
for the rest of his life.

15:14.914 --> 15:20.093
♪

15:20.136 --> 15:23.313
- Do the surgery.
- Good.

15:23.357 --> 15:24.532
I just need the two of you
to sign

15:24.575 --> 15:25.533
some consent forms, please.

15:27.709 --> 15:30.538
- Hey.
- Yeah?

15:30.581 --> 15:32.322
- Dr. Archer is the best.

15:33.628 --> 15:34.629
- Okay.

15:34.672 --> 15:38.589
♪

15:38.633 --> 15:41.505
[indistinct chatter]

15:45.161 --> 15:46.597
- Hey, Doris?
- Yeah?

15:46.641 --> 15:47.903
- What's going on over here?

15:47.947 --> 15:49.949
- You didn't see the tweet?
- What tweet?

15:49.992 --> 15:51.124
- Wes Tucker's sister.

15:51.167 --> 15:52.603
She asked people to come in
and see

15:52.647 --> 15:54.214
if they're a match to donate
a piece of their liver.

15:54.257 --> 15:56.216
All these people
are lining up for Wes?

15:56.259 --> 15:57.304
- Yep.

15:58.914 --> 16:02.483
- We're not taking a liver from
another deserving candidate.

16:02.526 --> 16:05.921
We'd be taking a section
of liver from a living donor.

16:05.965 --> 16:09.577
It's great publicity for live
donorship and the hospital.

16:09.620 --> 16:11.274
- He can't stop drinking,

16:11.318 --> 16:13.842
which means he's likely to ruin
his transplant within months.

16:13.885 --> 16:15.583
- Yes, we have a patient

16:15.626 --> 16:17.672
suffering from
alcohol abuse disorder,

16:17.715 --> 16:19.630
but with therapy and medication

16:19.674 --> 16:23.025
it's possible Mr. Tucker
can maintain his sobriety.

16:23.069 --> 16:25.680
- Okay, let's talk about
the potential donors.

16:25.723 --> 16:27.160
This is a complicated surgery

16:27.203 --> 16:29.162
with a long
and difficult recovery.

16:29.205 --> 16:31.164
- They've been apprised
of the risks.

16:31.207 --> 16:33.166
They're trying
to save a man's life.

16:33.209 --> 16:37.300
- Dr. Blake, Dr. Marcel,
please give us a moment.

16:37.344 --> 16:39.302
- Sure.
- Thank you.

16:44.307 --> 16:47.223
- Dr. Shentu, this hospital
runs on the expertise

16:47.267 --> 16:50.792
and dedication of our doctors,
and I cannot stand by

16:50.835 --> 16:57.494
and watch their medical
opinions being ignored.

16:57.538 --> 17:01.107
- Ms. Goodwin, if the donor
were a family member,

17:01.150 --> 17:02.673
there'd be no argument,

17:02.717 --> 17:05.067
but because they don't
personally know Mr. Tucker,

17:05.111 --> 17:07.548
there's an issue?
I don't see why.

17:07.591 --> 17:11.595
- And as you've said
more than one time,

17:11.639 --> 17:14.642
it's good publicity
for the hospital.

17:14.685 --> 17:21.605
♪

17:24.565 --> 17:26.828
- All right,
Weitlaner receptor.

17:26.871 --> 17:28.090
Thank you.

17:31.833 --> 17:33.095
- Hold on. What is that?

17:33.139 --> 17:35.750
- Getting a better look here.

17:35.793 --> 17:37.447
It's a mass.

17:37.491 --> 17:40.363
It's coming from up
around the elbow.

17:40.407 --> 17:44.237
Mm, I'm afraid we might be
looking at a synovial sarcoma.

17:44.280 --> 17:46.413
- Any chance it's benign?

17:46.456 --> 17:49.329
- It's possible.
I've seen crazier things.

17:49.372 --> 17:52.506
- But you don't think it is?

17:52.549 --> 17:53.681
- No, I don't.

17:56.466 --> 17:59.121
All right, well, let's get
this thing out of here.

17:59.165 --> 18:00.427
- I'll go get
his parents' consent.

18:00.470 --> 18:02.690
- No, no, no, no.
We don't need consent.

18:02.733 --> 18:04.257
It's part of the surgery now.

18:04.300 --> 18:06.868
I got two bones to plate,
and I can't plate one of 'em

18:06.911 --> 18:08.391
unless the tumor's removed.

18:08.435 --> 18:09.653
- Dean, if their son
has cancer,

18:09.697 --> 18:11.438
I owe it to them
to tell them first.

18:11.481 --> 18:12.526
- Well, I hope
you're not opening up

18:12.569 --> 18:14.180
a can of worms with this,
Dr. Scott.

18:14.223 --> 18:16.138
But if you gotta be
a boy scout, then do it fast.

18:16.182 --> 18:18.923
Okay. Radial plate.

18:18.967 --> 18:20.838
[alarm blares]
- What happened?

18:20.882 --> 18:21.970
- She became short of breath

18:22.013 --> 18:23.102
as I was hanging
a bag of saline.

18:23.145 --> 18:24.233
- Help me.

18:24.277 --> 18:25.408
- She's not protecting
her airway.

18:25.452 --> 18:27.628
Get me 20 of Etomidate,
100 of suts.

18:27.671 --> 18:30.631
Nadia, I'm gonna place a tube
to help you breathe.

18:30.674 --> 18:31.632
- What's going on?

18:31.675 --> 18:33.112
- She's in respiratory
distress,

18:33.155 --> 18:34.330
but it doesn't make sense.

18:34.374 --> 18:35.766
She's been responding
to her antibiotics,

18:35.810 --> 18:37.159
her fever's coming down.

18:37.203 --> 18:38.943
- It's from the silicone.

18:38.987 --> 18:40.815
- What?
- A silicone embolus.

18:40.858 --> 18:42.469
The implant must have leaked

18:42.512 --> 18:45.124
and infiltrated
the vascular system.

18:45.167 --> 18:46.647
[tense music]

18:46.690 --> 18:48.214
- He might be right.

18:48.257 --> 18:50.041
Could have gotten into a vessel
and shot up in her lungs.

18:50.085 --> 18:52.392
I'm in. Bag.

18:52.435 --> 18:55.177
We need to get her up
for a CT angiogram stat.

19:00.313 --> 19:01.662
- Hold on.
- Please.

19:01.705 --> 19:03.664
- No, I don't think
I can let you go up there

19:03.707 --> 19:07.537
because you're not actually
Nadia's father, are you?

19:09.365 --> 19:11.498
You're her surgeon.

19:11.541 --> 19:15.806
♪

19:20.463 --> 19:20.855
.

19:20.898 --> 19:22.509
- Hey, Maggie.

19:22.552 --> 19:23.814
Maggie?
- Oh.

19:23.858 --> 19:25.555
- Hey.
- Hey, Sharon.

19:25.599 --> 19:30.343
- You okay?
- Yeah. It's nothing.

19:30.386 --> 19:34.564
Vanessa's parents invited me
to dinner tonight.

19:34.608 --> 19:36.087
They wanna get to know me.

19:36.131 --> 19:41.092
- Wow. That's a big step.
But it could be good.

19:41.136 --> 19:43.747
- Sharon, I just sprang myself
on those people.

19:43.791 --> 19:45.445
I don't know
what they think of me.

19:45.488 --> 19:47.098
- Well, you know, I kinda see

19:47.142 --> 19:49.579
why you'd be
a little apprehensive.

19:49.623 --> 19:51.929
- Vanessa's so excited.

19:51.973 --> 19:54.715
- So what are you gonna do?

19:54.758 --> 19:57.892
[apprehensive music]

19:57.935 --> 19:59.894
- Hey, how's Darius doing?

19:59.937 --> 20:02.244
- Not good.
Just got the path report.

20:05.987 --> 20:09.033
- Is he done yet?
- He's not.

20:09.077 --> 20:12.863
Unfortunately, during
the surgery, we found a mass.

20:12.907 --> 20:14.430
It's a cancer
of the soft tissue

20:14.474 --> 20:15.953
called a synovial sarcoma.

20:15.997 --> 20:17.651
- Oh no, wait,
I don't--I don't understand.

20:17.694 --> 20:18.826
- Wait, you know,
he's 10 years old.

20:18.869 --> 20:20.349
He--he can't have cancer.

20:20.393 --> 20:21.785
- I--I know this is a lot,

20:21.829 --> 20:23.265
but right now we need
to remove the tumor

20:23.309 --> 20:25.354
and then follow up
with oncology.

20:25.398 --> 20:26.747
- Oh, my God.

20:26.790 --> 20:28.488
- No, no, no, no,
I--I want another doctor.

20:28.531 --> 20:30.011
I want another doctor.

20:30.054 --> 20:30.968
- Terrell,
there's no time, man.

20:31.012 --> 20:32.143
He's under general and--

20:32.187 --> 20:33.623
- He's done working
on my son, okay?

20:33.667 --> 20:35.103
- Terrell!
- Okay.

20:35.146 --> 20:37.279
Nobody's cutting into Darius
just 'cause you say so.

20:37.323 --> 20:40.456
[tense music]

20:40.500 --> 20:45.244
♪

20:45.287 --> 20:48.290
- So now where do you
practice exactly?

20:48.334 --> 20:50.988
- At first I practiced
in Russia.

20:51.032 --> 20:53.077
I was a doctor
to many businessmen

20:53.121 --> 20:55.906
and politicians,
very successful.

20:55.950 --> 20:57.256
- But then you moved
to the States,

20:57.299 --> 20:59.388
and then where did you
get your training here?

20:59.432 --> 21:01.608
- I was forced to leave
my country,

21:01.651 --> 21:02.957
and I could not afford

21:03.000 --> 21:05.307
to spend 10 years
doing another residency.

21:05.351 --> 21:06.656
- So just to be clear,

21:06.700 --> 21:08.876
you never received
a license to practice here.

21:08.919 --> 21:11.008
- People in my community
trusted me

21:11.052 --> 21:13.446
with earaches, sore throats.

21:13.489 --> 21:16.275
- Not exactly talking about
an earache here.

21:16.318 --> 21:18.015
- My people need me.
What can I do?

21:18.059 --> 21:20.061
- Gee, I don't know.

21:20.104 --> 21:21.584
Refer 'em to
a qualified physician?

21:21.628 --> 21:25.849
- The surgery I did was good.
It was the implants.

21:25.893 --> 21:27.155
- That you got off
the black market

21:27.198 --> 21:28.678
because
you don't have a license.

21:28.722 --> 21:35.859
♪

21:36.904 --> 21:39.080
- I need to make a call.

21:42.170 --> 21:43.954
- There's another patient.

21:43.998 --> 21:46.305
Says he operated
on another young woman same day

21:46.348 --> 21:48.785
using implants
from the same bad batch.

21:48.829 --> 21:50.396
- So her implants
could be leaking too then.

21:50.439 --> 21:51.745
- Name's Alexandra.

21:51.788 --> 21:53.094
She's not picking up,
but we have this address.

21:53.137 --> 21:54.443
- We may not have much time.

21:54.487 --> 21:56.271
If she throws an embolus,
she could stroke out.

21:56.315 --> 21:57.838
- I'll grab the transport team
and head out.

21:57.881 --> 21:59.056
- No, wait, they just
brought a patient back

21:59.100 --> 22:00.841
in the stroke truck, take that.

22:02.799 --> 22:04.366
- So what do we do with him?

22:04.410 --> 22:05.889
- I'll take care of that.

22:11.199 --> 22:13.854
- Dean, we got a problem.

22:13.897 --> 22:15.116
- What?

22:15.159 --> 22:16.509
- Terrell refused
the excision.

22:16.552 --> 22:18.728
- Are you kidding me?

22:18.772 --> 22:20.687
I mean, we never needed consent
in the first place.

22:20.730 --> 22:22.384
- Yeah, I know, but now that

22:22.428 --> 22:24.386
one parent told us to stop,
we don't have a choice.

22:24.430 --> 22:26.214
- I never should have let you
take this case.

22:26.257 --> 22:27.389
- Dean.

22:27.433 --> 22:28.912
- I cannot keep this boy
under forever,

22:28.956 --> 22:30.087
so here's what's gonna happen.

22:30.131 --> 22:32.176
I'm gonna finish
the radial plate,

22:32.220 --> 22:35.092
and you got 20 minutes to get
Terrell to change his mind.

22:35.136 --> 22:37.356
Yeah, you told me
you were his friend.

22:37.399 --> 22:40.576
So take off your white coat
and talk to him.

22:40.620 --> 22:43.971
Drill.
[drill whirring]

22:44.014 --> 22:48.410
- Dr. Blake, Dr. Marcel.

22:48.454 --> 22:49.977
I just wanted you to know

22:50.020 --> 22:52.022
they found a live donor
match for Wes.

22:52.066 --> 22:53.937
And in light of your opinion

22:53.981 --> 22:55.983
that the transplant
is inadvisable,

22:56.026 --> 22:58.377
they've asked Dr. Jones
to perform it instead.

22:58.420 --> 23:00.161
- He's never done
a split liver transplant.

23:00.204 --> 23:01.597
Dr. Blake here
is the only one who has.

23:01.641 --> 23:04.470
- I understand,
but the decision's been made.

23:04.513 --> 23:06.297
- And what did Ms. Goodwin
say about this?

23:06.341 --> 23:08.517
- She voiced her concerns
strenuously,

23:08.561 --> 23:11.564
but the board overruled her.
We're moving forward.

23:14.131 --> 23:15.785
- Wait, that's the donor?

23:15.829 --> 23:18.527
- It is.
- No, no. That's my patient.

23:18.571 --> 23:21.487
Listen, he had a panic attack
this morning.

23:21.530 --> 23:22.618
He's not in a position

23:22.662 --> 23:24.533
to be making
any major life decisions.

23:24.577 --> 23:27.449
I mean, resecting
a portion of his liver?

23:27.493 --> 23:30.844
- I'm sorry, but he's a match
and he volunteered.

23:33.542 --> 23:35.936
- I can't let him do this.
- You heard him.

23:35.979 --> 23:38.155
There's nothing
we can do about it,

23:38.199 --> 23:40.506
except to hope
that Jones doesn't kill him.

23:45.511 --> 23:48.209
- Hey, Terrell.
Look, man, we gotta talk.

23:48.252 --> 23:49.471
- I got nothing to say
to you, man.

23:49.515 --> 23:51.560
- If this about back
when I was a cop, I--

23:51.604 --> 23:52.909
- Yeah, and you arrested me!

23:52.953 --> 23:54.476
- I was just one of the cops
on the scene, bro.

23:54.520 --> 23:55.782
I didn't know you were
gonna be in that house.

23:55.825 --> 23:57.131
- Would you get
outta here with that, Dylan?

23:57.174 --> 23:59.220
You watched them
put them cuffs on me.

24:04.704 --> 24:06.445
- Look, man, uh...

24:08.403 --> 24:09.448
I'm sorry.

24:10.884 --> 24:12.929
- Sorry?

24:12.973 --> 24:16.019
You sorry? We were a team, man.

24:16.063 --> 24:17.499
The three of us,
best of friends,

24:17.543 --> 24:19.109
but you had to go off
with Carmen.

24:19.153 --> 24:21.068
[solemn music]

24:21.111 --> 24:22.896
Then you watched me get busted.

24:22.939 --> 24:25.072
I mean, what kind of friend
is that?

24:26.987 --> 24:28.771
- All right.

24:28.815 --> 24:30.512
You right.

24:30.556 --> 24:32.253
I could've been
a better friend to you.

24:34.385 --> 24:36.518
But this is not about that.

24:37.911 --> 24:39.042
You got a sick kid upstairs,
man.

24:39.086 --> 24:41.218
- Hey, man, don't.

24:41.262 --> 24:43.090
- He's got cancer, Terrell!

24:47.050 --> 24:49.139
You his father.

24:49.183 --> 24:50.663
He needs you to make
the right call, bro.

24:50.706 --> 24:54.057
- I don't need you to tell me
something I already know.

24:56.582 --> 24:58.192
- Hate me.

24:58.235 --> 25:00.455
Hate me as much
as you want, bro.

25:01.978 --> 25:03.371
But I ain't walking away until

25:03.414 --> 25:04.764
I get your consent
for that surgery.

25:04.807 --> 25:11.945
♪

25:13.337 --> 25:15.122
- Do it.

25:25.132 --> 25:28.396
[tense music]

25:28.439 --> 25:30.224
- Alexandra?

25:35.011 --> 25:36.622
Take it in.

25:40.408 --> 25:42.323
Alexandra?

25:42.366 --> 25:43.716
Alexandra? Can you hear me?

25:45.761 --> 25:47.589
Alexandra? Talk to me.

25:50.984 --> 25:52.159
Bag her.
Let's get her on the truck.

25:52.202 --> 25:57.120
♪

26:01.734 --> 26:01.908
.

26:01.951 --> 26:03.953
- Ready to roll in a minute.
- All right.

26:03.997 --> 26:05.694
- How's she doing?
- Not good.

26:05.738 --> 26:07.435
I intubated her,
and she's in septic shock.

26:07.478 --> 26:08.741
Did you get the CT yet?

26:08.784 --> 26:11.265
- The image just came up.

26:11.308 --> 26:13.702
There's a silicone embolus
in her right ventricle

26:13.746 --> 26:15.661
partially obstructing
the outflow tract.

26:15.704 --> 26:18.098
- Oh, my--this is bad.

26:18.141 --> 26:20.796
If it shifts, it could
occlude the valve and kill her.

26:20.840 --> 26:22.668
We gotta move right now.
Let's go.

26:22.711 --> 26:24.713
- No, wait. You can't drive.

26:24.757 --> 26:26.323
The smallest bump
could dislodge it.

26:26.367 --> 26:27.324
- Hold on.
- We don't have a choice.

26:27.368 --> 26:28.630
We have to get her to IR.

26:28.674 --> 26:30.632
- Will, you could do
the extraction there.

26:30.676 --> 26:31.894
- In the truck?
There's no way.

26:31.938 --> 26:32.982
I--I'd be going in blind.

26:33.026 --> 26:34.593
- No, you could
take serial CTs

26:34.636 --> 26:35.898
as you thread the catheter up.

26:35.942 --> 26:37.291
I'll read them
and guide you through it.

26:37.334 --> 26:38.422
- Stevie, in case you forgot,

26:38.466 --> 26:39.902
I'm not an interventional
radiologist.

26:39.946 --> 26:41.382
I could cause an arrhythmia.

26:41.425 --> 26:43.079
I mean, I could perforate
a vessel, no way.

26:43.123 --> 26:44.733
- Will, if that silicone
shoots into her valve

26:44.777 --> 26:46.430
and you're not
in this hospital,

26:46.474 --> 26:49.564
we won't have time to save her.

26:49.608 --> 26:51.305
It's our only option.

26:51.348 --> 26:54.308
[tense music]

26:54.351 --> 26:55.918
♪

26:55.962 --> 26:58.225
- All right.
Get the extraction kit.

27:01.707 --> 27:04.318
- Hey, Mr. Shaw.
- Hey, doc.

27:04.361 --> 27:05.928
- How you feeling?

27:05.972 --> 27:07.451
- I'm okay.

27:07.495 --> 27:08.844
- That's good.

27:10.106 --> 27:14.328
So I--I hear
you're going into surgery.

27:14.371 --> 27:15.503
- Did you see?

27:15.546 --> 27:17.374
They're covering
the story on the news.

27:17.418 --> 27:18.811
- Right.

27:18.854 --> 27:20.813
- My Instagram is blowing up.

27:23.424 --> 27:25.948
- Well, look, I gotta ask,

27:25.992 --> 27:28.647
are you sure
you wanna go through with this?

27:28.690 --> 27:30.823
- Dr. Marcel, I have always

27:30.866 --> 27:33.477
wanted to do something
meaningful with my life.

27:33.521 --> 27:36.567
And then this lands in my lap.

27:36.611 --> 27:37.917
- But?

27:39.570 --> 27:41.050
- But I--I guess

27:41.094 --> 27:43.139
I didn't realize
what a big operation it is.

27:43.183 --> 27:46.795
And--and--and then
only having half a liver,

27:46.839 --> 27:49.493
and that list
of possible complications

27:49.537 --> 27:51.495
I had to sign,
it was pretty long.

27:51.539 --> 27:52.671
- Yeah.

27:54.629 --> 27:57.240
Well, you know,
you can still back out.

27:57.284 --> 27:58.677
No one's gonna blame you.

28:01.505 --> 28:02.506
- I know.

28:02.550 --> 28:04.639
[sentimental music]

28:04.683 --> 28:06.597
But this is Wes Tucker.

28:08.034 --> 28:10.079
He's gonna have a piece of me
keeping him alive.

28:12.778 --> 28:14.910
I have to do this.

28:18.348 --> 28:21.221
- Excuse me guys. Excuse me.

28:21.264 --> 28:22.483
Pamela?
- Mm?

28:22.526 --> 28:24.833
- Come here.

28:24.877 --> 28:27.357
Look, you should do
the transplant.

28:27.401 --> 28:29.185
Miles is my patient,
which means I need to fight

28:29.229 --> 28:31.666
for whatever's best for him.
And right now that's you.

28:31.710 --> 28:32.841
- Crockett, don't think
I haven't been

28:32.885 --> 28:35.017
struggling with this, I have.

28:35.061 --> 28:37.019
I wish there was an easy
answer, but there just isn't.

28:37.063 --> 28:39.456
- Okay, but the fact is,
the transplant's happening,

28:39.500 --> 28:41.502
and you have
the most expertise.

28:41.545 --> 28:43.547
As chief of the department,
you have every right,

28:43.591 --> 28:46.681
and I think an obligation
to take it over.

28:46.725 --> 28:47.769
Please.

28:47.813 --> 28:50.729
[apprehensive music]

28:50.772 --> 28:51.817
- Can you get everyone
outta here,

28:51.860 --> 28:54.167
prep OR seven and open a trace?

28:54.210 --> 29:00.303
♪

29:00.347 --> 29:01.522
- About to thread the wire.

29:01.565 --> 29:03.132
You sure we don't
need radiology?

29:03.176 --> 29:06.396
- No, it's okay.
I can see where you are.

29:06.440 --> 29:09.095
Okay, go slow and steady.

29:09.138 --> 29:12.054
You've got 10 centimeters until
you're at the right ventricle.

29:12.098 --> 29:14.753
- All right, 10 centimeters.
Threading the wire.

29:18.931 --> 29:20.410
How many CTs can we get?

29:20.454 --> 29:21.803
- I'm not sure.

29:21.847 --> 29:23.239
You grabbed us before
we had a chance to refuel,

29:23.283 --> 29:25.372
and we've never done
a test in here before.

29:27.417 --> 29:29.202
- Okay, 10 centimeters.
Let's get one.

29:32.292 --> 29:35.121
- Great.
The silicone is right there.

29:35.164 --> 29:37.601
Turn 120 degrees.

29:37.645 --> 29:39.168
- Okay. Turning.

29:40.866 --> 29:42.084
- Will, something's happening.

29:42.128 --> 29:43.738
- She bradying down.
Rate's in the 50s.

29:43.782 --> 29:45.131
- Get another image.

29:45.174 --> 29:47.524
[alarms beeping]

29:47.568 --> 29:51.572
Stevie, what's going on?
- The silicone. It's moved.

29:51.615 --> 29:53.269
It's obstructing
the pulmonary valve.

29:53.313 --> 29:54.923
She's not getting any blood
to her lungs.

29:54.967 --> 29:56.359
- If it's in the valve,
I can't grab it.

29:56.403 --> 29:58.405
- No, you'll have to float
the wire around it,

29:58.448 --> 29:59.536
inflate the balloon and then

29:59.580 --> 30:01.060
pull it back
into the ventricle.

30:01.103 --> 30:03.149
- It's not gonna be easy.
Image.

30:03.192 --> 30:08.545
♪

30:08.589 --> 30:12.375
- Okay, five degrees
to your right then inflate.

30:12.419 --> 30:14.987
- Sats at 71,
pressure's dropping fast.

30:16.423 --> 30:17.816
- I think I'm there. Image.

30:17.859 --> 30:20.296
[machine whirring, chirping]

30:20.340 --> 30:21.820
What's happening?

30:21.863 --> 30:23.952
- Can't do it--not enough
juice for another shot.

30:23.996 --> 30:25.780
- No, no, no.
You gotta be kidding me.

30:25.824 --> 30:27.651
- Hey, it's okay.

30:27.695 --> 30:29.262
I've been mapping you
the whole time, you're there.

30:29.305 --> 30:31.568
- Stevie, we are only gonna get
one shot at this.

30:31.612 --> 30:34.006
- You gotta trust me, Will.

30:35.529 --> 30:37.270
- Okay.

30:37.313 --> 30:44.233
♪

30:50.413 --> 30:51.850
Pulling back.

30:54.853 --> 30:56.506
[machine beeps]

30:56.550 --> 31:00.641
- Sats back up to 86, rate's
back into 70, sinus rhythm.

31:00.684 --> 31:02.730
- Nice job, Dr. Halstead.

31:04.645 --> 31:06.386
- All right, Lauren.
Let's roll.

31:06.429 --> 31:08.518
- All right. Let's go.

31:08.562 --> 31:09.955
- How's Darius doing?

31:09.998 --> 31:12.740
- Arch is up there now
removing the tumor.

31:12.783 --> 31:16.657
- So you got Terrell to agree?
- Yeah.

31:16.700 --> 31:20.574
- I guess there's still
something between you guys.

31:20.617 --> 31:24.926
- Nah, he didn't do it for me.
He did it for his son.

31:24.970 --> 31:27.929
[pensive music]

31:27.973 --> 31:34.893
♪

31:34.936 --> 31:36.068
- Scalpel.

31:36.111 --> 31:38.722
[apprehensive music]

31:38.766 --> 31:42.509
♪

31:42.552 --> 31:43.553
Dr. Marcel?

31:43.597 --> 31:45.207
- Yeah.
- Where are you?

31:45.251 --> 31:46.905
- Clamping that
hepatic artery now.

31:46.948 --> 31:48.994
[machines beeping]

31:49.037 --> 31:50.691
You watching that
heart rate, Marty?

31:50.734 --> 31:52.519
- I gave him 4
of dobutamine.

31:52.562 --> 31:53.955
I can't get his rate above 60.

31:53.999 --> 31:55.478
- Oh, come on.
- Is everything okay?

31:55.522 --> 31:58.873
- He's hypertensive.
- Heart rate 52, BP 81/59.

31:58.917 --> 32:00.788
- He keeps bradying down,
and I can't stop it.

32:00.831 --> 32:03.660
- Is he bleeding?
- No. No bleeding.

32:03.704 --> 32:05.227
- Well, nothing else
makes sense.

32:05.271 --> 32:08.056
Vagal nerve stimulation?
Anesthesia sensitivity?

32:08.100 --> 32:10.929
- Wait a second.
His beta blockers.

32:10.972 --> 32:12.191
He takes 'em when he's nervous.

32:12.234 --> 32:13.627
He must have taken it
before surgery,

32:13.670 --> 32:15.281
and now it's slowing his heart.
[machines beeping]

32:15.324 --> 32:16.456
- He's coding.

32:16.499 --> 32:18.937
- Check the pulse.

32:18.980 --> 32:20.808
We got no pulse
- Defib.

32:20.851 --> 32:22.201
- Charge the paddles to 200.

32:22.244 --> 32:24.072
- Okay, starting compressions.

32:25.813 --> 32:27.467
- Charging.
- Clear.

32:30.557 --> 32:31.775
[machine beeps]

32:31.819 --> 32:32.820
- No pulse.

32:32.863 --> 32:33.821
- Give me an amp of epi,

32:33.864 --> 32:34.996
charge the paddles to 200.

32:35.040 --> 32:37.868
- Charging.
- Clear.

32:37.912 --> 32:39.740
[machine beeps]

32:39.783 --> 32:42.482
- Sinus rhythm,
rate's back to 55.

32:44.788 --> 32:47.617
- Okay, so beta blockers
have a half-life of four hours.

32:47.661 --> 32:49.793
What do you wanna do?

32:49.837 --> 32:53.014
- Marty,
put in a temporary pacer.

32:53.058 --> 32:55.756
We've come this far,
we might as well ride it out.

32:55.799 --> 32:59.716
♪

32:59.760 --> 33:02.154
- Slow and stop.

33:02.197 --> 33:04.939
You got it? Hold it steady.

33:08.029 --> 33:09.596
- How's she doing?

33:11.990 --> 33:14.166
- It's still too early to tell.

33:14.209 --> 33:16.255
But, uh,

33:16.298 --> 33:18.431
I don't know
about this one, Stevie.

33:18.474 --> 33:25.394
♪

33:27.353 --> 33:29.355
- Was that Alexandra?
- Yep.

33:29.398 --> 33:31.357
- She had an embolus too?
- Uh-huh.

33:34.664 --> 33:38.364
- Look, I know you judge me,

33:38.407 --> 33:39.756
but in my country,

33:39.800 --> 33:41.715
I was persecuted.
I had to flee.

33:41.758 --> 33:43.195
- I understand.

33:43.238 --> 33:44.370
But it doesn't give you
the right to come over here

33:44.413 --> 33:46.154
and do plastic surgery
out of a garage.

33:46.198 --> 33:48.330
- They would've gone
to someone else.

33:48.374 --> 33:50.028
Someone just looking
to take their money.

33:50.071 --> 33:51.420
At least I know what I'm doing.

33:51.464 --> 33:53.118
- Oh you do, do you?
You know what you're doing?

33:53.161 --> 33:55.120
- I'm a surgeon!
Show some respect.

33:55.163 --> 33:58.253
- No, you were a surgeon
back in Russia, right?

33:58.297 --> 33:59.863
Where you worked at a hospital

33:59.907 --> 34:01.561
that had proper
medical equipment.

34:01.604 --> 34:02.605
What you're doing here,

34:02.649 --> 34:05.043
it is illegal,
and it isn't safe.

34:05.086 --> 34:06.696
Do you even get that?

34:06.740 --> 34:08.568
I mean, at this point,
you're gonna be damn lucky

34:08.611 --> 34:10.091
if those two women survive.

34:10.135 --> 34:16.924
♪

34:19.144 --> 34:21.015
I'm sorry.
You left me no choice.

34:24.888 --> 34:26.890
- I never meant to hurt anyone.

34:26.934 --> 34:34.072
♪

34:38.902 --> 34:39.077
.

34:39.120 --> 34:42.036
- Want Mommy to tuck you in
like I do at home?

34:42.080 --> 34:43.733
Like a sausage?

34:43.777 --> 34:46.649
Two saus--
[knock at door]

34:46.693 --> 34:48.086
Hey.

34:48.129 --> 34:51.741
- Hey, what's up, D-man?
Uh-oh. Bulls colors, right?

34:51.785 --> 34:56.268
Uh-huh. I see you. Mm-hmm.

34:56.311 --> 34:57.704
- Hey.
- Hey.

34:57.747 --> 35:00.010
- I know you talked to Terrell,

35:00.054 --> 35:03.492
and I can't thank you enough.
- Oh, of course.

35:09.411 --> 35:11.587
- Mommy will be
right back, okay?

35:11.631 --> 35:14.547
[apprehensive music]

35:14.590 --> 35:17.463
♪

35:17.506 --> 35:20.335
Darius has a long way to go,
doesn't he?

35:20.379 --> 35:23.295
- Unfortunately, I think so.

35:23.338 --> 35:26.124
Oncology will be down tomorrow
to set up a treatment plan.

35:26.167 --> 35:29.692
It'll likely involve
chemotherapy, radiation.

35:29.736 --> 35:33.000
But Darius can beat this.

35:35.133 --> 35:39.789
I want you to know
I'm here for you, and him.

35:39.833 --> 35:41.139
Okay?

35:43.532 --> 35:45.317
- Thank you.

35:45.360 --> 35:50.539
♪

35:50.583 --> 35:54.543
- Dylan, stay away
from my family.

36:00.114 --> 36:02.203
- Hey.
- Hey.

36:02.247 --> 36:04.684
- Hey. What's up, champ?

36:09.254 --> 36:13.214
- Dr. Halstead, what are you
doing here this late?

36:13.258 --> 36:16.174
- Offsite release forms
and insurance paperwork.

36:16.217 --> 36:20.134
- You mean for going out
and saving that young woman?

36:20.178 --> 36:21.527
- Yep.

36:21.570 --> 36:24.225
- Did our compliance officer
make you do this?

36:24.269 --> 36:25.748
- Yeah, and something about

36:25.792 --> 36:29.012
the hospital
being under a microscope.

36:30.013 --> 36:31.189
- Huh.

36:34.148 --> 36:37.238
[tense music]

36:37.282 --> 36:39.588
♪

36:39.632 --> 36:41.024
Ms. Quinn.

36:43.679 --> 36:45.768
Naming my doctors
on this lawsuit

36:45.812 --> 36:47.248
is weighing them down

36:47.292 --> 36:49.642
and keeping them
from their jobs.

36:49.685 --> 36:51.600
They didn't do anything wrong.

36:51.644 --> 36:53.254
- I'm not on a witch hunt,
Ms. Goodwin,

36:53.298 --> 36:55.387
but every person associated
with the Vas-COM

36:55.430 --> 36:56.823
needs to be held accountable.

36:56.866 --> 36:59.347
- Okay, so then what's
going to happen?

36:59.391 --> 37:02.655
You investigate them one by one
until their names

37:02.698 --> 37:03.786
drop off your list.

37:03.830 --> 37:05.745
So let's just cut to the chase.

37:05.788 --> 37:09.270
Take their names
off your lawsuit now,

37:09.314 --> 37:11.141
and hold me accountable.

37:11.185 --> 37:14.275
- Do your attorneys know
that you're doing this?

37:14.319 --> 37:17.496
- No, they do not.

37:17.539 --> 37:18.801
- And you understand the burden

37:18.845 --> 37:21.064
of what you're
getting yourself into.

37:21.108 --> 37:22.457
- I do.

37:22.501 --> 37:23.676
So.

37:26.679 --> 37:29.682
Ask me everything
you want to know.

37:37.559 --> 37:40.258
- Hey.
- How's Nadia?

37:40.301 --> 37:41.520
- Much better.

37:41.563 --> 37:45.175
Her fever's coming down,
and Alexandra's too.

37:46.960 --> 37:49.615
- Good.
- Yeah.

37:51.094 --> 37:54.794
Well, enjoy the rest
of your day off.

37:54.837 --> 37:56.709
- I still have
a couple hours left.

37:58.450 --> 38:01.496
Would you wanna go
bowling tonight?

38:01.540 --> 38:02.845
Well, I am dressed, after all,

38:02.889 --> 38:05.587
and I do have
the shoes in the car.

38:06.675 --> 38:08.590
- Yeah, sure.

38:08.634 --> 38:10.679
Just give me
a few minutes to finish up.

38:10.723 --> 38:13.334
- Great.
- Dr. Hammer?

38:13.378 --> 38:14.814
I have a delivery for you.

38:14.857 --> 38:16.903
- Mm, thanks.
- Sign here.

38:30.917 --> 38:33.180
- You okay?
- Yeah, it's nothing.

38:33.223 --> 38:37.097
It's just--it's paperwork
for my divorce.

38:37.140 --> 38:38.881
- Oh.

38:38.925 --> 38:40.622
Didn't know you were married.

38:40.666 --> 38:44.278
- It's over.
He's just dragging it out.

38:44.322 --> 38:47.237
[pensive music]

38:47.281 --> 38:50.284
- Yeah, maybe we should
do this another night.

38:53.766 --> 38:56.029
- Maybe we should.
- Yeah.

38:58.597 --> 39:00.729
All right. I'll see you.

39:00.773 --> 39:07.780
♪

39:09.521 --> 39:12.306
[rock music playing]

39:12.350 --> 39:14.352
- What's up? Whiskey, neat.

39:19.357 --> 39:20.358
Thank you. Thank you.

39:29.018 --> 39:30.716
- The past always comes back
to bite you in the ass,

39:30.759 --> 39:33.414
doesn't it?

39:33.458 --> 39:35.024
- I guess so.
- Yeah.

39:36.635 --> 39:38.245
You and Darius's mom, huh?

39:39.681 --> 39:44.643
- Yeah, 12 years ago.
Good thing. I screwed it up.

39:44.686 --> 39:46.732
- I know--I know
what that's like.

39:49.169 --> 39:51.911
My son hasn't spoken
to me in 15 years.

39:54.087 --> 39:57.220
[soft sentimental music]

39:57.264 --> 39:58.918
♪

39:58.961 --> 40:00.746
- It does. Thank you.
- Can have the bread?

40:00.789 --> 40:03.618
- Oh yeah, sure, here.

40:03.662 --> 40:04.793
- Mm-hmm.

40:04.837 --> 40:08.623
- So I hear
your husband's a teacher.

40:08.667 --> 40:10.233
- Yeah. He is.

40:10.277 --> 40:12.322
- Mm-hmm.

40:12.366 --> 40:15.717
Ben.
He's a fourth grade teacher.

40:15.761 --> 40:17.806
That's why he couldn't
be here tonight,

40:17.850 --> 40:19.068
parent-teacher conference.

40:19.112 --> 40:21.593
- Hmm.
I never liked those much.

40:21.636 --> 40:23.769
Always got anxious.

40:23.812 --> 40:25.335
But you know how it is,

40:25.379 --> 40:27.903
you always do anything
for the kids.

40:31.167 --> 40:33.082
- Yeah.

40:33.126 --> 40:34.475
You do.

40:34.519 --> 40:40.089
♪

40:40.133 --> 40:43.441
- Bea, you really outdid
yourself with this lasagna.

40:43.484 --> 40:44.572
- Mm-hmm.
- Thanks.

40:44.616 --> 40:46.661
- Delicious.

40:46.705 --> 40:48.446
And is that turkey
that I'm tasting?

40:48.489 --> 40:49.534
- Yes, it is.

40:49.577 --> 40:51.884
I find it's lighter
than sausage.

40:51.927 --> 40:54.364
- You're right.

40:54.408 --> 40:58.238
- Um, I could send you
the recipe if you'd like.

41:00.980 --> 41:02.242
- That would be great.

41:02.285 --> 41:09.249
♪

41:17.866 --> 41:20.782
[dramatic music]

41:20.826 --> 41:27.963
♪

41:47.896 --> 41:51.030
[wolf howls]
